				<h2>Substance Use</h2>
				<p><b>Tobacco</b>
				<p>The negative health consequences of smoking are real. Heart disease, cancer, emphysema – these conditions can occur among youth who smoke. 
				<p>Smoking affects the quality of your life. It makes your clothes stink, it makes your breath stink (which makes you less kissable, just saying) and it’s expensive (more than $10 a pack in the City). Smoking will also shorten a person’s life by an average of 15 years. 
				<p>It’s not just smoking that hurts you. Chew, smokeless tobacco such as paan or gutkha, bidis, hookahs and kreteks are not safe alternatives. Despite their tasty flavors and perfume-like smells, these products contain hazardous toxins similar to regular cigarettes and can lead to the same negative health effects such as various types of cancer, bronchitis, lung disease, heart disease and asthma.

				<p><b>Alcohol and Other Drugs</b>
				<p>For most people, substance abuse and addiction have their beginnings in adolescence. Whether it’s alcohol, tobacco, ex, or weed, some researchers think that early experiments may have a bigger impact during adolescence because your brain is still growing and developing.  
				<p>Adults also worry because substance use - even casual weekend goofing - can lead to problems at school and home, the loss of friends and community support, lasting legal trouble, and other serious consequences. It can kill you. How?
				<p>Drugs and alcohol distort your ability to reason and impair your decision-making. It makes planning and calculating risk more difficult if not impossible. It also makes you more susceptible to suggestion and peer pressure, which increases the likelihood of unprotected sex, unintended pregnancies and STIs. Binge drinking and substance abuse can lead to reckless driving, resulting in injury or death, and suicides, violence, and drowning. 
				<p>If you need to talk to someone about your situation, there are adults who want to help. If you can’t get the help you need at home, a teacher, counselor, or school nurse are good people to turn to. They can help get the support you need to sort things out.			
				
      		</div>
    	</div>
 	</div> 

   	  
